      <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m a first-year PhD @&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cityu.edu.hk/&#34;&gt;CityUHK&lt;/a&gt;, advised by &lt;a href=&#34;https://ningmiao.space&#34;&gt;Ning Miao&lt;/a&gt;. Previously, I worked as a master student @&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.fudan-disc.com/&#34;&gt;Fudan DISC&lt;/a&gt; (affiliated to &lt;a href=&#34;https://nlp.fudan.edu.cn/nlpen/main.htm&#34;&gt;FudanNLP&lt;/a&gt;), advised by &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.fudan-disc.com/people/zywei&#34;&gt;Zhongyu Wei&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://siyuanwangw.github.io/&#34;&gt;Siyuan Wang&lt;/a&gt;. I was a research intern @&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.xlang.ai/&#34;&gt;XLANG&lt;/a&gt;, advised by &lt;a href=&#34;https://taoyds.github.io/&#34;&gt;Tao Yu&lt;/a&gt;. I earned my bachelor&amp;rsquo;s degree from @&lt;a href=&#34;https://english.bit.edu.cn/&#34;&gt;Beijing Institute of Technology&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My works mainly focus on reward design (ALaRM, HaF-RM) and evaluation (DS-1000, ARKS) with an emphasis on reasoning. I&amp;rsquo;m particularly interested in the efficient oversight of human-level/superhuman models.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
